headline: MGP (MGPI) Q2 Earnings and Revenues Top Estimates
summary: MGP (MGPI) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of +51.56% and +5.59%, respectively, for the quarter ended June 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Bud Profit Rises. Why AB InBev Stock Is Plummeting After Earnings.
summary: Anheuser-Busch InBev  stock plummeted even though the brewer reported quarterly earnings which, on the surface, didn’t look all that bad.  The company, which sells household brands including Budweiser, Bud Light, Corona, Michelob, and Stella Artois said its profit rose to $1.67 billion in the quarter, up about 14% from the same period last year.  Second-quarter underlying earnings per share (EPS) came in at 98 cents on revenue of $15 billion.
